House Bill 537
By: Representative Blackmon of the 146th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 8 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to sales
2 and use taxes, so as to provide for the maximum amount of local sales and use taxes that may
3 be imposed; to revise provisions related to a special district sales and use tax; to provide for
4 conditions under which such tax may be imposed; to provide for clarifications; to provide for
5 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 8 of Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to sales and use
9 taxes, is amended in Code Section 48-8-6, relating to prohibition of political subdivisions
10 from imposing various taxes, ceiling on local sales and use taxes, and taxation of mobile
11 telecommunications, by revising subsection (a) as follows:
12 "(a)(1) Except as provided in this subsection, on and after July 1, 2024, there shall not
13 be imposed in any jurisdiction in this state or on any transaction in this state local sales
14 taxes, local use taxes, or local sales and use taxes in excess of 2 percent. For purposes
15 of this such 2 percent limitation, the taxes affected are any sales tax, use tax, or sales and
16 use tax which is levied in an area consisting of less than the entire state, however
