48 SECTION 2.
49 Said chapter is further amended by revising Code Section 48-8-109.31, relating to imposition
50 of special sales and use tax within special district and limited time and purpose, as follows:
51 "48-8-109.31.
52 (a) Subject to the requirement of approval by local referendum and the other requirements
53 of this article, to impose there may be imposed within any given special district a special
54 sales and use tax for a limited period of time for the limited purpose of property tax relief.
55 (b) Except as to rate, a tax imposed under this part shall correspond to the tax imposed by
56 Article 1 of this chapter. No item or transaction which is not subject to taxation under
57 Article 1 of this chapter shall be subject to a tax imposed under this article, except that a
58 tax imposed under this article shall apply to sales of motor fuels as prepaid local tax as
59 defined in Code Section 48-8-2 and shall be applicable to the sale of food and food
60 ingredients and alcoholic beverages as provided for in Code Section 48-8-3.
61 (c) The special sales and use tax provided for in subsection (a) of this Code section may
62 be imposed by a special district in 0.05 percent increments, but in no event shall such tax
63 exceed 1 percent in total. The levy of such tax upon sales of motor fuels as defined in
64 Code Section 48-9-2 shall only be imposed on the retail sales price of the motor fuel which
65 is not more than $3.00 per gallon.
66 (d)(1) As a condition precedent to the issuance of the call for the referendum:
67 (A)(1) The governing authority of the county whose geographical boundary is
68 conterminous with that of the special district and the governing authority or authorities
69 of all municipalities that levy an ad valorem tax on property, other than those
